etc: configuraton files
var: files are expected to grow or change, sys & app logs
bin: executables for boot and processes
sbin: exec for root users
lib: bin for systems
usr: exec for the users 
cat /etc/passwd
adduser <new_user>
sudo passwd -e <user>
drwxr--r--:w => dir owen: read, write, exec & group: read & everyone : read
r=4, w=2 et x=1
sudo chgrp root .bash_history
sudo chown root .bash_history

Firewall for a server
sudo ufw default deny incoming (deny everything comming)
sudo ufw default allow outgoing (allow everything server is sending)
sudo ufw 2222/tcp (allow tcp in port 2222)
sudo ufw enable (to activate firewall)

sudo service apache2 start => Launch Apache2
There used to be a webpage in localhost 80.
